name: Agony of Defeat
description: Snatching loose change from the jaws of defeat.

name: Stick Shift
description: Learn how to create custom goals for your games!

name: Walk It Off
description: A long walk; can we speed this up?

name: Turns
description: Just follow the shore and you'll be ok.

name: Steps
description: Go more than one step at a time.

name: The Gem
description: Learn how to code your hero!

name: Two Gems
description: Move a little further to grab two gems!

name: Big Gem Square
description: Go more than one step at a time.

name: Go Around
description: Can't go through it? Go around it.

name: Doors
description: It's the crates that need to hide from you.

name: Open and Shut
description: Crates. You know what to do.

name: One Block
description: You can change go block directions.

name: One at a Time
description: Try to fight enemies one at a time. You can only take two hits right now.

name: Heart Up
description: There's a heart to be had!

name: Choose Your Battles
description: You can't beat three at once.

name: Tough
description: Three hearts is better than two.

name: No Keys
description: Who keeps leaving these crates around?

name: Knock Knock
description: You can hit crates to break them open.

name: Careful
description: Discretion is the better part of valor.

name: Spin to Win
description: Use spin to hit everything around you.

name: Whirlwind
description: Now that's what I'm talking about.

name: Twister
description: They are no match for your special moves!

name: Kaboom
description: Sometimes you just need some big explosions.

name: Two Big
description: Your hit does 2 damage, and these enemies each have 4 health.

name: Zap It
description: You can use zap to hit enemies from far away for 1 damage.

name: Hit and Spin
description: You can use hit for dragonflies and spin for crabs.

name: Busy Intersection
description: Small enemies are no match for your spin.

name: Advantage
description: Good thing that river is there!

name: Back Up
description: You might want to stand back a bit further.

name: Badder Guy
description: Dragonflies have more health. Use hit to do more damage than spin.

name: Hit Me Up
description: Combining zap and hit? That's good tactics.

name: Lure It
description: We're going to need to lure it out.

name: Tornado
description: Nothing shall stand in your way!

name: More Times
description: Increase loop repeat counts to repeat more times.

name: Chain Reaction
description: Oh, this is going to be fun.

name: Restraint
description: Don't repeat your loop too many times!

name: Fern
description: Think about how many times to loop and to move.

name: Smasher
description: Break through barriers without breaking a sweat.

name: Zap Master
description: There sure are a lot of monsters in this challenge.

name: Loopy
description: You can use loops to repeat your code.

name: Tall Wave
description: Loops can contain more complicated movement patterns.

name: Right Up
description: You can add code to the end of a loop.

name: Clearing the Way
description: Loop your way through the explosives.

name: Friends
description: You're not alone on these islands.

name: Spin Eternally
description: Use spin in a for-loop to escape a pack of skeletons.

name: Careful Aim
description: Be careful what you blow up.

name: Scratch Loop
description: Create your own loops from scratch.

name: Down the Line
description: Practice filling in empty loop bodies.

name: Detonations
description: These TNT blocks aren't going to explode themselves.

name: If Only
description: Use if to decide what to do.

name: Seer
description: Use look to see what is around you.

name: Short and Tall
description: One loop, two loops, short loop, tall loop.

name: Loop Before
description: You can put loops before other code.

name: Crab Nest
description: Clear out a swarm of crabs.

name: Gem Weave
description: Use loops to weave through the halls and gems.

name: Lurker
description: There's something waiting for you at the end.

name: Loop Middle
description: You can put loops in between other code.

name: Dragonfly Nest
description: You can nest loops inside each other.

name: Loot Loop
description: Add a loop to grab the gems.

name: Loop After
description: You can put loops after other code.

name: Double Loop
description: You can use two loops in one program.

name: Showdown
description: The monster is charging. It's just you and your trusty for-loop.

name: Both Sides
description: Grab gems on both sides, if they are there.

name: Look Past It
description: Look twice in the same direction.

name: Take That
description: See the cubes behind the gems.

name: Decisions
description: Check the type of what you see.

name: To and Fro
description: Back and forth, looking for gems.

name: Strike Force
description: Fight each monster the right way.

name: Why Did
description: Use != to avoid blowing up chickens.

name: While Time
description: Use while loops to repeat code while you see something.

name: No One
description: While loops are more flexible than loops with fixed counts.

name: Control Time
description: Who needs to count any more?

name: Waits For
description: While loops repeat with built-in if checks.

name: If Master
description: Loop look loop, loop look loop!

name: Crate Rows
description: Lots of crates to bust through. Were they full of gems?

name: Zap Until Chicken
description: Use while to just zap until you see a chicken.

name: Tunnel Vision
description: Look up and decide what to do.

name: Whiling Away
description: While loops can be inside other while loops.

name: Don't Hit Gems
description: Gems are fragile. Other things needs hitting.

name: Feathers
description: No need to count your chickens with while loops.

name: The Chicken
description: Zap this! Zap that! But don't zap chickens.

name: Cube Conditions
description: You can nest loops within ifs within loops.

name: Cross the Ocean
description: Sure are a lot of chickens here.

name: Keep Going
description: Use while within while to keep looking for gems.

name: Tireless
description: You can heal inside a loop.

name: Scratch Scratch
description: Any injury is just a scratch now.

name: Go the Distance
description: The distance function returns the number of empty squares in a direction.

name: Zags
description: Use distance to move the right amounts.

name: While Master
description: While not enough while loops: write more while loops.

name: Set to Blast
description: Zap anything you want, just don't blow up the world.

name: Into the Jello
description: Never again fear the gelatinous cube.

name: While Inside
description: Write nested while loops from scratch.

name: Healer
description: Use heal to restore your health.

name: Tough Enough
description: Four hearts is enough to beat a cube!

name: Catching Breath
description: Heal while your health is less than 4.

name: Return Distance
description: Go back while distance is greater than 0.

name: Scattered
description: Distance lets you handle more complicated movements.

name: Vary All
description: More variables! Variables for everything! Vary all the things!

name: Greater Hero
description: Distance lets you handle more complicated movements.

name: Code Master
description: You are ready for the ultimate coding challenge.

name: Not My Type
description: You can use variables where you can use strings.

name: Type Variables
description: Variables can store type strings like "crab".

name: Set Your Steps
description: Create a steps variable to count your steps.

name: Zap Smart
description: Save variables and then move to zap explosives near enemies.

name: More Variables
description: You can name variables whatever you want.

name: Memory
description: Remember how far you moved, so you can move back.

name: Variables
description: Variables are like labeled boxes where your code stores things it needs to remember.

name: Look and See
description: Variables let you remember what you saw before.

name: Step Boxes
description: You can use variables to remember stuff in your code.

name: Very Vary
description: Use = to set a variable's value.

name: Stylish Intent
description: Begin learning how to style various elements of a webpage.

name: Orders Wanted
description: Create numbered lists of the world's most wanted ogres and friends.

name: Classy
description: Get classy and individually style groups of elements!

name: Identification, Please
description: Identify and control specific elements on the page.

name: Wanted Poster
description: Create a wanted poster with HTML and CSS.

name: Listing Liaison
description: Organize list elements efficiently without using breaks.

name: Dangerous Divide
description: Learn how to group information on websites with wonderful dividing powers!

name: Big and Tall
description: Images can be any shape or size. Big and tall, or small and stout.

name: Illustrious Imagery
description: The web has more than just text. Add images! Be illustrious.

name: Headliner
description: Label content using header tags, so everyone knows what is to follow.

name: Paragraph Paragon
description: Learn a better way of grouping content using paragraphs!

name: Breaking News
description: Break your ideas into nice, bite-sized chunks.

name: Humble Beginnings
description: Begin the journey to becoming an expert web developer! Change text and watch your webpage grow.

name: JavaScript: Master of Names
description: Use your new coding powers to target nameless enemies.

name: JavaScript: Lost in the Stacks
description: Use code blocks to find your way out of the library.

name: JavaScript: Patrol Buster
description: Defeat ogre patrols with new, selective targeting skills.

name: JavaScript: Fire Dancing
description: Save typing (and your hero) with loops!

name: JavaScript: Back to Back
description: Patrol the village entrances, but stay defensive.

name: JavaScript: Maniac Munchkins
description: Defend yourself while munchkins attack! Break open a chest and take the spoils.

name: JavaScript: True Names
description: Learn an enemy's true name to defeat it.

name: JavaScript: A Fine Mint
description: Ogre Peons are trying to steal your coins! Don't let them snag your rightful earnings!

name: JavaScript: Return to Thornbush Farm
description: Ogres are invading again, and the only cure is more parameters!

name: Query Confirmed
description: Get introduced to the basics of the web's most popular library: jQuery.

name: Clickthrough
description: Interactive elements are a staple of the web!

name: Disappearing Act
description: Make elements vanish and appear! Astound your enemies, bewilder your friends.

name: Toggulation
description: Toggle classes, on and off, to create improve interactability in the page!

name: Eventful Selectors
description: Use a single event listener to act on multiple elements.

name: Sibling Rivalry
description: Select an element's neighbors to control the neighborhood!

name: Border Patrol
description: Adding borders to elements helps separate them from other elements.

name: Marginal Utility
description: Margins and padding are used to separate content.

name: Transformative Properties
description: Rotate, scale, or move elements using transform!

name: Animania
description: Animation is about squishing and squashing elements!

name: Precision Coloring
description: Specify specific shades of colors using the rgb() CSS function!

name: Quizlet
description: Create a quiz of questions and group them using pseudo-psychological methods!
